      "procedure": "1. Divide students into two teams.\n2. Write each vocabulary word on a separate slip of paper.\n3. One student from each team picks a word and acts it out without speaking.  For 'gesture,' they might wave or bow. For 'emotion,' they could show sadness or happiness. For 'express,' they might mime writing a letter. For 'encounter,' they could act out meeting someone unexpectedly. For 'significant,' they could point to a ring or a meaningful object.\n4. Their team tries to guess the word within a time limit.\n5. Teams take turns until all vocabulary words have been acted out.",
